<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-736-701  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 736 701.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 18 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Gov't approves Control Data Corp mainframe sale to China.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Control Data Corp. (Contracts).andO;Ticker:    CDA.andO;Product:   Control Data Cyber 992 (Mainframe computer) (Purchasing).andO;Topic:     Computer industryChina. State Meteorological AdministrationGovernment AgencyGovernment ContractsGovernment RegulationInternational TradeMainframe computers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GOV'T APPROVES CONTROL DATA CORP MAINFRAME SALE TO CHINA 12/18/90MINNEAPOLIS, MINNESOTA U.S.A., 1990 DEC 18 (NB) --Control Data Corp (CDC) hasreceived an export license from the Bush administration to ship one of theirCYBER 992 computers to China.andM;The Chinese government says the machine will be used by the StateMeteorological Administration to improve regional weather forecasting.andO;Charlotte Fransen, public relations manager for CDC told Newsbytes that thetotal contract would be in excess of $7 million.andM;The model 992 is believed to be the highest performance computer the USgovernment has ever approved for sale to China.andP;  The multilateralCoordinating Committee on Export Controls (COCOM) still must approve the salebefore the export license can be issued.andP;  Approval is expected in early 1991,and CDC plans to install the computer shortly thereafter.andM;COCOM approval is required because it exceeds the present guidelines forChina, under which computers cannot exceed a Processing Data Rate (PDR) of550 megabits per second.andP;  The limit is intended to exclude the possibility ofcomputers being used for military applications.andP;  The CYBER 992 is rated at aPDR of 2030.andP;  CDC says it expects the US government to require securitymeasures to insure its computer is dedicated to civilian weather forecastingonly.andP;  The CYBER 992 is considered the minimum strength computer necessaryfor comprehensive weather forecasting.andM;The Chinese weather agency currently uses a smaller CYBER 960 for limitedweather analysis.andP;  It will be used in conjunction with the new system.andO;Forecasts made with the help of the new system will be broadcast to civilianpopulations within and outside China, in both Chinese and English.andP;  Data andforecasts will also be distributed to the world weather community to benefitother major weather centers.andM;It is estimated that in an average year, severe weather adversely affectsabout 200 million Chinese, and that about 1700 people are killed in variousweather disasters.andM;(Jim Mallory/19991217/Press Contact: Charlotte Fransen, Control Data,612-853-6137)</TEXT></DOC>